  <TITLE> ideal_dm  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE> May, 2006 </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="ideal_dm"> construct a ideal deformable mirror.  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[dm]=ideal_dm(ap,act_arr)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>ap  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the aperture of the deformable mirror. </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>act_arr </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the actuator array of the deformable mirror</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>dm  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the output deformable mirror. </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    construct a ideal deformable mirror. The dynamic model for the motion of the 
    actuators does not contain any fancy motion, such as: hysteresis, and uses 
    a constant velocity approximation to move the actuators.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
	ap=circle(5);
	act_dim=8;act_pitch=1;act_vel=1e-4;
	act=actuator_array(act_dim,act_dim,act_pitch,act_vel);
	dm=ideal_dm(ap,act);
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
